T1  - Notes on Tension Discharge Rates as an Employee Health Status Predictor
AU  - Matteson, Michael T.
AU  - Ivancevich, John M.
Y1  - 1983/09/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256266
DO  - 10.5465/256266
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 540
EP  - 545
VL  - 26
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses a study pertaining to the validity of the tension discharge rate scale (TDR) for measuring employee health status. The scale utilizes a 7-point response format and is designed to discriminate among a number of health, personality, and life factors. The TDR scale was compared with other employee health status measurement techniques. Experts say the TDR results were tentative and incomplete. They explain that it is unclear what TDR measures. The relationship between job stress and TDR scores was unable to be determined.
AB  - The article discusses a study pertaining to the validity of the tension discharge rate scale (TDR) for measuring employee health status. The scale utilizes a 7-point response format and is designed to discriminate among a number of health, personality, and life factors. The TDR scale was compared with other employee health status measurement techniques. Experts say the TDR results were tentative and incomplete. They explain that it is unclear what TDR measures. The relationship between job stress and TDR scores was unable to be determined.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256266
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256266
Y2  - 2026/04/24
