T1  - Apples and Oranges: An Empirical Comparison of Commonly Used Indices of Interrater Agreement
AU  - Jones, Allan P.
AU  - Johnson, Lee A.
AU  - Butler, Mark C.
AU  - Main, Deborah S.
Y1  - 1983/09/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256262
DO  - 10.5465/256262
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 507
EP  - 519
VL  - 26
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Empirical comparison of common indices of interrater agreement indicated that the indices are not directly comparable in regard to the magnitude of the estimates produced or the information conveyed. Some of the indices may be severely distorted if applied to homogeneous sets of ratings. Although analyses of ratings at an item level might suggest inadequate agreement, composites of those items may yield satisfactory indications of interrater agreement.
AB  - Empirical comparison of common indices of interrater agreement indicated that the indices are not directly comparable in regard to the magnitude of the estimates produced or the information conveyed. Some of the indices may be severely distorted if applied to homogeneous sets of ratings. Although analyses of ratings at an item level might suggest inadequate agreement, composites of those items may yield satisfactory indications of interrater agreement.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256262
