T1  - Managerial Strategies in Municipal Government Organizations
AU  - Stevens, John M.
AU  - McGowan, Robert P.
Y1  - 1983/09/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256264
DO  - 10.5465/256264
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 527
EP  - 534
VL  - 26
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses a study pertaining to managerial strategies in municipal government organizations. The findings indicate that there are multiple internal and external strategy approaches used by managers. The study results suggest that the internal and external actions of public managers are interrelated. Experts say public managers are influenced by multiple parties including federal and state governments, constituents, and clients. The overall strategy of public managers is comprised of contingency elements. The management patterns appear to be based on a risk-averse approach.
AB  - The article discusses a study pertaining to managerial strategies in municipal government organizations. The findings indicate that there are multiple internal and external strategy approaches used by managers. The study results suggest that the internal and external actions of public managers are interrelated. Experts say public managers are influenced by multiple parties including federal and state governments, constituents, and clients. The overall strategy of public managers is comprised of contingency elements. The management patterns appear to be based on a risk-averse approach.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256264
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256264
Y2  - 2026/04/24
