N2  - The present study investigated whether a contrast effect was operating in making judgments about and issuing rewards to engineers and scientists. It was found that the greater the proportion of unsatisfactory performing engineers, the more favorable the engineering supervisors' performance ratings and reward practices. Similar findings were not found for the scientist sample.
